Transfer a Work Item to a Different Skill Set

You can transfer a work item to a different skill set so that an agent with the right skills can resolve the issue. For example, if an agent doesn’t have the right skills to resolve the case, the agent can transfer the case and specify the required skills.

REQUIRED USER PERMISSIONS
To transfer work items to a different skill: Skills-based routing must be enabled and set up in your org

When an agent opens the transfer dialog and searches for skills, the search process looks for matching skills. The search results show matching skills from only the first 2,000 skills that were created.

Work items are transferred to an agent who has the required skills. When a work item is transferred, the status changes to Transferred. If no agent with the required skills is available, the work item isn’t assigned and is shown in the Skills Backlog Tab in Omni Supervisor.

The transfer icon doesn’t appear in Enhanced Omni-Channel. You can create a similar result by adding an action on the appropriate record page, an action that executes a screen flow to route skills to appropriate targets.

Click the transfer icon.
The transfer dialog is displayed. The transfer dialog shows the skills that are already attached to the work item.
Search for the skill that the work item needs.
To add the skill to the work item, select the skill.
You can add several skills to the work item. For example, you could select billing and Spanish for a case that needs a Spanish-speaking agent who’s knowledgeable about your company’s billing practices.
Click Transfer.

For skills-based routed chats, the Transfer icon is on the work item on the My Work tab in the Omni-Channel component.
title: Transferring Work Items to Different Skill Sets in Service Cloud
